25 "(a) Upon receipt of notice of conviction of any person of a motor vehicle moving offense,
26 such offense having been committed while such person's driving privilege was in a state of
27 suspension or revocation, the Division shall revoke such person's driving privilege for an
28 additional period of time as set forth in subsection (b) hereof. For purposes of this section a
29 violation of G.S. 20-7(a), 20-24.1, or 20-28(a) G.S. 20-7(a) or G.S. 20-28(a) or (a2) shall not be
