32 SECTION 3.(h) G.S. 20-217(g2) reads as rewritten:
33 "(g2) Pursuant to G.S. 20-54, failure of a person to pay any fine or costs imposed pursuant
34 to this section shall result in the Division withholding the registration renewal of a motor vehicle
35 registered in that person's name. The clerk of superior court in the county in which the case was
36 disposed shall notify the Division of any person who fails to pay a fine or costs imposed pursuant
37 to this section within 40 days of the date specified in the court's judgment, as required by
38 G.S. 20-24.2(a)(2). judgment. The Division shall continue to withhold the registration renewal
39 of a motor vehicle until the clerk of superior court notifies the Division that the person has
40 satisfied whichever of the following conditions of G.S. 20-24.1(b) are applicable to the person's
41 case.case:
42 (1) Disposes of the charge in the trial division in which the person failed to appear
43 when the case was last called for trial or hearing.
44 (2) Demonstrates to the court that the person is not the person charged with the
45 offense.
46 (3) Pays the penalty, fine, or costs ordered by the court.
47 (4) Demonstrates to the court that the person's failure to pay the penalty, fine, or
48 costs was not willful and that the person is making a good-faith effort to pay
49 or that the penalty, fine, or costs should be remitted.
50 The provisions of this subsection shall be in addition to any other actions the Division may
51 take to enforce the payment of any fine imposed pursuant to this section."
