48 PART V. REPEAL COURT COSTS FOR SEAT BELT INFRACTIONS
49 SECTION 5.(a) G.S. 20-135.2A(e) reads as rewritten:
House Bill 722-First Edition Page 7

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "(e) Any driver or front seat passenger who fails to wear a seat belt as required by this
2 section shall have committed an infraction and shall pay a penalty of twenty-five dollars and fifty
3 cents ($25.50) plus the following court costs:($25.50).
4 (1) The General Court of Justice fee provided for in G.S. 7A-304(a)(4).
5 (2) The fee provided for in G.S. 7A-304(a)(2a).
6 (3) One dollar and fifty cents ($1.50) to be remitted to the county wherein the
7 infraction was issued, except in those cases in which the infraction was issued
8 by a law enforcement officer employed by a municipality, the fee shall be paid
9 to the municipality employing the officer.
10 (4) One dollar and fifty cents ($1.50) for the supplemental pension benefits of
11 sheriffs to be remitted to the Department of Justice and administered under
12 the provisions of Article 12H of Chapter 143 of the General Statutes.
13 Any rear seat occupant of a vehicle who fails to wear a seat belt as required by this section
14 shall have committed an infraction and shall pay a penalty of ten dollars ($10.00) and no court
15 costs. Conviction of an infraction under this section has no other consequence."
16 SECTION 5.(b) This section becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to costs
17 and fees assessed on or after that date.
