19 PART VI. MANDATORY EXEMPTION FROM PROBATION SUPERVISION FEE
20 WHEN PROBATION IS EXTENDED FOR THE SOLE PURPOSE OF COMPLYING
21 WITH MONETARY OBLIGATIONS
22 SECTION 6.(a) G.S. 15A-1343(c1) reads as rewritten:
23 "(c1) Supervision Fee. – Any person placed on supervised probation pursuant to subsection
24 (a) of this section shall pay a supervision fee of forty dollars ($40.00) per month, unless exempted
25 by the court. The court may exempt a person from paying the fee only for good cause and upon
26 motion of the person placed on supervised probation. The court shall exempt a person from
27 paying the fee when probation is extended for the sole purpose of complying with monetary
28 obligations. No person shall be required to pay more than one supervision fee per month. The
29 court may require that the fee be paid in advance or in a lump sum or sums, and a probation
30 officer may require payment by such methods if he is authorized by subsection (g) to determine
31 the payment schedule. Supervision fees must be paid to the clerk of court for the county in which
32 the judgment was entered, the deferred prosecution agreement was filed, or the conditional
33 discharge was ordered. Fees collected under this subsection shall be transmitted to the State for
34 deposit into the State's General Fund."
35 SECTION 6.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
36 supervision fees incurred in the calendar month after that date and all subsequent supervision
37 fees incurred in the same term of supervised probation.
38
39 PART VII. EFFECTIVE DATE
40 SECTION 7. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
41 law.
